# {{projectName}}

This is a **NONoise multi-repo workspace** — an umbrella that hosts N git
sub-repositories under `repos/` and orchestrates them via a root-level
`repositories.json` manifest plus a small set of scripts.

Scaffolded with [create-nonoise](https://github.com/russosalv/NONoise) v{{frameworkVersion}}.

## Quickstart

1. Open `repositories.json` at the workspace root and replace the placeholder
   entry with the real sub-repos (set `"status": "active"` for each one).
2. Run the bootstrap script:

   ```bash
   # macOS / Linux / Git Bash
   ./scripts/clone-all.sh

   # Windows PowerShell
   ./scripts/clone-all.ps1
   ```

3. Open the workspace root in your editor. AI tools (Claude Code, Copilot, etc.)
   will pick up the `.claude/skills/` tree that ships with the workspace.

## Managing sub-repos

All scripts live under `scripts/` and come in both `.sh` and `.ps1` flavors.

### `clone-all`

Clones every active sub-repo declared in `repositories.json` into `repos/<path>/`.
Already-cloned sub-repos are skipped. Safe to re-run whenever you add a new
entry to the manifest.

```bash
./scripts/clone-all.sh
# or
./scripts/clone-all.ps1
```

### `switch-branch`

Puts every active sub-repo onto the same branch. If the branch exists locally
it's checked out; otherwise it's tracked from `origin/`; otherwise it's created
(optionally from a base branch). Uncommitted changes are auto-stashed.

```bash
./scripts/switch-branch.sh feature/123-my-feature
./scripts/switch-branch.sh feature/123-my-feature --base develop --fetch

# PowerShell
./scripts/switch-branch.ps1 -BranchName feature/123-my-feature
./scripts/switch-branch.ps1 -BranchName feature/123-my-feature -BaseBranch develop -FetchFirst
```

### `pull-all`

Runs `git pull --ff-only` in every active sub-repo.

```bash
./scripts/pull-all.sh
# or
./scripts/pull-all.ps1
```

## Working inside a single sub-repo

By default this workspace is **workspace-centric**: the `.claude/skills/` tree
lives only at the workspace root, and you open the workspace root with your AI
tool to access every skill (including Polly, the SDLC orchestrator). Sub-repos
under `repos/` are managed as plain git repositories with no embedded skill tree.

### Escape hatch

If you prefer having the full `.claude/` tree inside a specific sub-repo (for
example, you want to work on one sub-repo in isolation with its own AI context),
copy it manually:

```bash
cp -r .claude repos/<path>/.claude
# PowerShell
Copy-Item -Recurse .claude repos/<path>/.claude
```

NONoise ships workspace-centric by default; there is no automation for this
step on purpose — it's an explicit choice the developer makes per sub-repo.

## VibeKanban compatibility

VibeKanban supports umbrella workspaces with multiple sub-repos as long as they
are colocated in a single tree and can be aligned onto the same branch. Running
`./scripts/switch-branch.sh <branch>` before a VibeKanban task makes the whole
workspace behave as one unit of work.

## Docs hierarchy

Like every NONoise project, this workspace ships with a standard `docs/` layout:

- `docs/architecture/` — source of truth: architectural decisions, patterns,
  component registry, cross-cutting rules for the whole workspace
- `docs/requirements/` — functional & business requirements (output of
  `requirements-ingest`)
- `docs/calls/` — meeting transcripts and notes
- `docs/support/` — reverse-engineering dossiers and reference material
- `docs/prd/` — product requirement documents (output of `arch-brainstorm`,
  validated by `arch-decision`)
- `docs/sprints/` — sprint manifests (output of `sprint-manifest`)

The standard NONoise SDLC flow is: `requirements-ingest` -> `arch-brainstorm` ->
`arch-decision` -> `sprint-manifest` -> `atr`. Invoke Polly (via `/polly` or
"start polly") any time you're unsure what to run next — Polly is the conductor
across the SDLC.

